fields.name: louboutin
fields.description: The Louis Orlato high-top sneaker is an iconic model by Maison Christian Louboutin and features a tone-on-tone rubber sole. This season, the upper, featuring sleek lines, combines smooth Loubi red calfskin suede and basket weave effect calfskin suede.

fields.name: Giuseppe Zanotti
fields.description: Giuseppe Zanotti fuses expert Italian craft with contemporary design in this pair of crocodile-embossed Frankie sneakers. Fashioned from leather, they are detailed with the label's signature side zip fastenings that run parallel to the central lace-up closure.

fields.name: Alexander Mcqueen
fields.description: White smooth calf leather lace-up sneaker with rounded toe and trimmed with lust red suede heel detail. Large flat laces and Alexander McQueen signature on tongue and heel counter. Oversized rubber sole.

fields.name: Fendi
fields.description: Slip on sneakers with a characteristic sock silhouette. Undulated rubber soles. Made of mesh with iconic FF motif. Black ribbed elastic edges. The details in rubberised film accentuate the silhouette of the shoe.

fields.name: Air Jordan 4 og bred
fields.description: Celebrating the 30th anniversary of the classic Air Jordan 4 silhouette, Air Jordan chooses its iconic OG Bred colourway Michael Jordan wore when he sank ‘The Shot’ during the first round of the 1989 NBA playoffs. Releasing in May 2019 the Air Jordan 4 OG Bred 2019 is rendered in a build that’s faithful to the original, complete with a black nubuck upper, visible Air-Sole cushioning underfoot and Nike Air branding on the heel. True to its name, this release is a true OG, and sometimes you can do nothing more than to marvel at an icon.

fields.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Black Metallic Gold
fields.description: Black and gold is one iconic colour combination you can depend on to always look good, and this pair of Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG GS Black Metallic Gold sneakers combines style with an unforgettable appearance. You get all the sophistication of classic black leather while showing off gold metallic accents to add gilding and personality. The collar flap is adorned with gold for striking bordering around the ankle, and a padded nylon tongue means a comfortable and versatile fit every time. The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG GS Black Metallic Gold stands out with its glossy black leather finish, and the silhouette is completed by intricate gold stitching along the black rubber sole for a truly special look. Black laces blend perfectly into the design whilst offering matte contrast against the sleek leather shine. Comfort meets class with this pair of sneakers.

fields.name: Jordan 1 Mids Low OG
fields.description: The Air Jordan 1 High 'Shattered Backboard' is one of the most iconic colourways to come out of the Jordan Brand camp. Fortunately, we are about to see the AJ1 low receive the Shattered Backboard treatment, guaranteeing to excite Jordan fans. This version of the AJ1 looks like a true throwback; white leather underlays are contrasted expertly by the eyecatching orange hue across the legendary Jordan panels. You can find the OG wings logo on the heel tab, whilst Nike Swoosh branding features across the lateral and medial sides of the shoe. Underfoot, a traditional Jordan 1 sole unit compliments the uppers perfectly dressed in a white and orange combination. This sole unit houses Nike Air technology, making this the perfect sneaker for the street or the courts

fields.name: Air Jordan 6 Retro Carmine
fields.description: Jordan Brand continues its stellar 2021, releasing a retro of the Jordan 6 in Michael Jordan's favourite colourway. The Carmine Jordan 6 has been worn multiple times by MJ himself, so we can all but guarantee these will be a fan favourite. The uppers are composed of a mix of red and white materials, making these the perfect shoe for Chicago Bulls fans. The padded ankle detailing features whilst the heel-pull tab also features in black and red. The iconic Jumpman logo features on the sneaker's heel while the shoe's tongue features the Jumpmana logo and the legendary pull-tab. Underfoot, a retro-looking sole unit houses Nike Air technology. The mix of black, white and silver emphasises the colourway perfectly. An air bubble features reminding all of us that Tinker Hatfield created this iconic silhouette. A real 90s throwback, be sure to add the Carmine to your collection.

fields.name: Air Jordan 4 Retro Lightning
fields.description: The Air Jordan 4 Retro GS Lightning 2021 is a premium pair of sneakers that no Air Jordan fan will want to miss — and now, in GS styling, smaller shoe sizes can enjoy such a quality design, too. This sneaker is made up of premium suede for a softer look and feel, coloured primarily in an eye-catching mustard yellow. This is balanced out by accents of white and grey, which are included on the midsole. The Air Jordan 4 Retro GS Lightning 2021 design is given extra texture and structure by the caged sidewalls, and you can depend on your usual cushioning with the sole’s Air unit. This is a bold and bright sneaker perfect for summer days that you can pair with any clothing item and make an impression and will be a firm favourite for those who prefer a suede texture to the usual leather.

fields.name: Air Jordan 4 Retro Fire Red 2012
fields.description: Did you miss the original release of the Air Jordan Retro Fire Reds? Have no fear, you can get your hands on this iconic colourway with the 2020 re-release of these fantastic sneakers. They’re not called fire red for anything, and the red styling set against the black and white detail work really brings the Air Jordan 4 Retro Fire Red 2012's to life. It’s not just the colouring either; the Air Jordan 4 Retros have always been a fan favourite because they combine great construction that's highly durable, with comfort and support whether you’re playing a game of hoops or kicking it on the street. Don’t miss the Air Jordan 4 Retro Fire Red 2012 sneakers this time around; they sell out quickly, so don't miss your chance to get your hands on a pair!

fields.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro High UNC X Off-White
fields.description: Taking inspiration from Michael Jordan's alma mater the May 2017 release of the Air Jordan 1 Retro High UNC x Off-White is dressed in a classic blue and white colourway a tribute to its source material and modelled on Virgil Abloh's deconstructed reimagining of the classic Air Jordan 1 silhouette. The detached wings and floating ‘Swoosh' with a touch of colour with exposed orange stitching is a now staple of Virgil's prototype Esq stylings that have become so successful with his Off-White releases. The handmade feel of the shoe and attention to detail makes the quality of this kickstand alone, and his dedication to delivering fresh takes on iconic silhouettes what makes people both reminiscent and excited about every new release.

fields.name: Nike Air Force 1 Low
fields.description: The Air Force 1 is the ultimate sneaker rotation staple, with every sneakerhead loving the OG basketball silhouette. Nike teams up with Undefeated to create a truly one-of-a-kind take on the classic shoe. The uppers are crafted from an eclectic mix of materials, with premium leather and suede both featuring. The underlays of the AF1 feature a mustard hue, whilst the legendary Air Force 1 panels come covered in a blue croc-like pattern. Nike and Undefeated co-branding features throughout, with the swoosh and undefeated logo both present on the shoe's lateral side. Down below, an intentionally aged Air Force 1 sole unit housing Nike Air technology completes the appearance of this must-have collaboration

fields.name: Nike Air Force 1 Low
fields.description: Released as part of Nike’s 2021 ‘Toasty’ pack, the Nike Women’s Air Force 1 Pecan Quilt takes the classic AF1 silhouette and elevates it with winter-ready fabrics, autumnal hues and the Air cushioning Nike is famed for. Inspired by wintery puffer jackets, the upper on this Air Force 1 is crafted from quilted fabrics in an orange, beige and brown colourway. Nike’s Swoosh sits in its usual place on the sidewalls and Tinker Hatfield’s Air cushioning is added underfoot to support you where you need it most. The perfect partner to all your chilly-weather outfits, add the Nike Air Force 1 Quilted to your collection while it’s still in stock!

fields.name: Air Jordan Retro High
fields.description: Jordan Brand returns once more with a women's exclusive Air Jordan 1 High, this time coming in an eye-catching court purple colourway. The AJ1 Court Purple features a minimalist white leather upper accentuated by pops of purple throughout. You can find the iconic Swoosh branding features across both lateral and medial sides of the shoe, whilst the Wings logo features on the sneaker's collar. You will also find the Nike Air logo on the shoe's tongue. Underfoot, Nike Air technology runs the length of the white and purple sole unit. This legendary technology guarantees unbeatable comfort whether you are wearing the silhouette on the court or the street. The Court Purple draws clear inspiration from the much anticipated Neutral Grey Air Jordan 1 released in February 2021. Fortunately, the Court Purple comes in smaller sizes giving everyone a chance to pick up a pair.

fields.name: Air Jordan 1 Mid University Blue Women's
fields.description: Are you hoping to stand out? The Air Jordan 1 Mid University Blue Women's sneakers are exactly what you're looking for. These blue, white, and black Air Jordan 1s have the styling you've come to expect, with the great University look and a classical silhouette that Air Jordans are famous for. It's not just the striking looks that you'll love about the Womens Air Jordan 1 Mid University Blue either; the fit is perfect, with a mid-height boot and ankle support that comes with a premium quality sneaker. Getting the colours right on these sneakers was the most important thing after considering a good construction, evident by the perfect combination of blue against black and white. The added winged Air Jordan logo in white really finishes the Air Jordan 1 Mid University Blue Womens, contrasting perfectly above to the Nike swoosh, which blends seamlessly into the black leather.

fields.name: Air Jordan 4 Retro
fields.description: It's been a minute since Virgil Abloh's Off White had dropped a sneaker with Nike, but it was most definitely worth the wait. The silhouette Virgil got his hands on this time around was the Air Jordan 4, a shoe he has not collaborated on before. We have seen this colourway on several occasions over the last yea

fields.name: Air Jordan 1 Low Chicago Flip
fields.description: Show off your love of the bold and the classic in the Air Jordan 1 Low Chicago Flip Womens. With rich shades of red dominating this timeless sneaker, complemented by clean white and glossy black, this is a sneaker you won’t want to miss. As always, this pair of Air Jordan 1s comes crafted with premium leather built with comfort in mind. The Nike Swoosh is presented in bright white to contrast cleanly against the black and red panelling, and you’ll find the Air Jordan logo in black against red on the heel of the Womens Air Jordan 1 Low Chicago Flip. From above, you get a clean white tongue, laces, and eyelet panel for a fresh, durable look, a theme that continues to the chunky mid and outer sole in classic white. Get your hands on a pair of Air Jordan 1 Low Chicago Flip Womens today!

fields.name: Air Jordan 1 Zoom CMFT
fields.description: Adding a touch of brown earth tones to pale pastel blue, this pair of Air Jordan 1 Zoom CMFT Psychic Blue Womens is an example of versatility at its best. This colour scheme is soft and palatable for any occasion or outfit, and the balanced supported design is ideal for all-day cushioning and comfort. The sleek leather panels combine a brushed suede effect for a softer look whilst adding subtle creases on the pastel blue leather. This is then combined with soft fabric mesh for the tongue and the collar for ultimate comfort. This colour palette brings to mind long days adventuring in the outdoors and luckily, the cushioned sole and balance of the Nike Air base means you can comfortably do so all day long. Soft brown laces complete the look, and air holes allow your feet to

fields.name: Air Jordan 1 Crimson Tint Retro
fields.description: Launching in April 2019 the Air Jordan 1 Crimson Tint Retro High OG shows us exactly why there is no better time to be a diehard fan of the Air Jordan 1 that right now. 2018 saw a seemingly endless stream of releases delight fans of the Jumpman brand, from high profile collaborations with industry heavy hitters, to remixed versions of iconic classics. This new Crimson Tint Jordan 1 iteration borrows a similar colour blocking to the timeless variety with black responsible for the vast majority of the Jordan 1 Crimson Tint's real estate, with ultra-premium tumbled leather adorning its upper. This shoe is another brilliant addition to an ever-growing catalogue of Jordan 1's that are going to fly off the shelves as soon as it is released.

fields.name: Air Jordan 1 Mid
fields.description: The Nike Dunk continues its pursuit of world domination with one of the best colourways we have seen. Drawing clear inspiration from the infamous UNC Jordans, we expect the White Aluminium Dunk to be a fan favourite. The uppers come crafted from premium leathers throughout, with white underlays contrasted by a powder blue hue covering the iconic Dunk paneling. Nike Swoosh branding features across both lateral and medial sides of the sneaker whilst a Nike Air logo features on the shoe's tongue. Down below, a traditional Dunk sole unit mirrors the uppers colourway and houses Nike Air technology. This technology has solidified the Dunks place as one of the most comfortable sneakers around and is one of the reasons skateboarders adopted the silhouette.

fields.name: Air Jordan Dunk Low
fields.description: Nike continues to push unbelievable colourways of its iconic Dunk silhouette, with the upcoming Laser Orange version perfect for the upcoming Summer months. The classic colour block combination is ever-present on this take of the Nike Dunk, with premium white leather underlays making up the foundation of the sneaker. The instantly recognisable panelling features in Laser Orange, making this one of the more eye-catching Nike Dunks to release. Other legendary Dunk details feature, such as the perforated toe box and Nike Air branding on the heel tab and tongue. You can also find swoosh detailing on the lateral and medial sides of the shoe. Underfoot, an original Dunk sole unit features in the same white and orange colour combination. This sole unit houses Nike Air technology making this one of the most comfortable sneakers on the market. An absolute must-have for sneakerheads worldwide

fields.name: Air Jordan 1 Low
fields.description: Nike is continuing with its earth-conscious mission, this time infusing 2021’s favourite silhouette with its Move to Zero fabrication. A sneaker that looks good and does good, the Nike Dunk Low Move to Zero Pink Womens combines crowd-favourite pastel hues with expertly designed cushioning and environmentally friendly materials. Unlike most other Nike Move to Zero offerings - which usually sport an earthy look and speckled sole - this Dunk stays true to Peter Moore’s original 1985 design with its perforated toe box, Swoosh branding and fabric tongue. The light grey outsole is the only hint that this kick is made with sustainability in mind, so you can do some good for the planet without sacrificing style. A key addition to your every-season rotation, a good-deed glow comes free with this Nike Dunk Low Move to Zero Pink.

fields.name: Air Jordan 1 Mid
fields.description: This pair of Air Jordan 1 Mid Multi Patent Womens combines not only a variety of colours but also a variety of fabric textures. This pair of sneakers comes with a colour palette bordering on retro vibes, with a vibrant combination of red, green, blue, grey, and orange, as well as an elegant black panelling that helps the other colours to stand out. The textured and layered appearance of this versatile sneaker is also made more interesting by the inclusion of glossy black leather as well as the coloured panels. The Nike swoosh stands out prominently in white against the rainbow of colours, and this works to match the white outer sole, which is cushioned for maximum comfort. Black laces work cohesively to run into the black leather panels, and the grey tongue adds a contrast at the top of the Womens Air Jordan 1 Mid Multi Patent.

fields.name: Air Jordan 1 Mid
fields.description: The Air Jordan 1 Mid SE Particle Beige Womens brings together the classic Air Jordan design with its stand-out elements, including the lightweight cushioning you’ve come to know and love. Comfort meets classic and soft beige in this sneaker. The mix of textures and leathers with the design of the Womens Air Jordan 1 Mid SE Particle Beige means a look that works cohesively together whilst offering a variety of shades and patterns. The various shades of beige attractively contrast with the white and black touches, which work to finish off this stylish pair of Air Jordans. The must-have black Nike swoosh stands out boldly against the softer tones of beige, and the black bordering along the top gives it a perfectly accentuated shape to work well with any outfit. The tan-coloured sole of the Air Jordan 1 Mid SE Particle Beige Womens finishes off this warm and versatile design

fields.name: Air Jordan 11
fields.description: Celebrating the iconic silhouettes 25th Birthday, we see the Jordan 11 release in a limited-edition Anniversary colourway. The sneaker made famous by Michael Jordan way back in 1995, this Jordan 11 is certain to turn the heads of passers-by. The sneaker comes composed from a mix of patent leather, mesh and natural leathers with these premium materials ensuring you get that luxurious vibe. You will find the iconic Jumpman logo on the heels of the shoe, coming in shiny, silver metal. In a further nod to the OG silhouette, Jordan lettering features on the shoe eyelets. One noticeable switch up, however, is the number 23 changes to 25 in honour of the anniversary. Underfoot, a white midsole is finished off with a translucent outsole. This sole houses Nike Air technology that will give you optimum comfort whether you are on the court or the street. This 25th Anniversary sneaker is most definitely going to hit grail status amongst Jordan enthusiasts, be sure to add them to your collection.

fields.name: Air Jordan 1 Mid
fields.description: The Jordan 1 Mid that for many put the silhouette on the map. A restock of one of the greatest Jordan 1 Mids is looming, and we could not be more excited. Melody Ehsani is a legendary designer from LA and put her stamp on the AJ1 back in 2019; the sneaker was an instant classic, so we are ecstatic to see the shoe re-releasing. The sneakers are perfectly mismatched, complete opposites of each other, but somehow it absolutely works. The left comes in a palette of greens and blues, whilst the right is composed of reds and oranges mostly. We see watch faces feature across the shoe's laces whilst graffiti working features around the outsole of each shoe. That same outsole houses the legendary Nike Air technology to guarantee unparalleled comfort wear after wear. This sneaker absolutely flew from the shelves the first time around and has been somewhat of a grail for many since. Don't make the same mistake twice; add this sneaker to your collection toda

fields.name: Air Jordan 6 Retro Gold
fields.description: This design for the Air Jordan 6s still remains true to Michael Jordan’s sixth sneaker style while offering a retro and gold update. The Air Jordan 6 Retro Gold Hoops sneaker, while embracing the timeless silhouette, includes tumbled leather panelling throughout in clean white. The sneaker includes layered panels to bring a textured look to the overall shoe, and the fresh white is balanced out by subtle inclusions of baby pink and metallic gold, all of which work perfectly together. This metallic gold is more prominently included on the gold hoops which are attached to the lacing panel. These gold hoops also include the Jumpman logo hanging down in an attractive accessory. The sole of the Air Jordan 6 Retro Gold Hoops combines an Air-cushioned midsole and a translucent rubber outer sole, both of which are built for maximum comfort

fields.name: Air Jordan 1 Mid
fields.description: The Air Jordan 1 Mid has been on a quest for sneaker domination over the last few years, with the latest colourway releasing, the Laser Orange, guaranteed to excite fans of the silhouette. Jordan Brand has taken this design slightly differently, with the iconic panelling on the shoe coming perforated in a unique twist we haven't seen too often. The ankle collar and toe box feature in the Laser Orange hue, whilst the underlay of the swoosh features in white. The legendary swoosh comes in black, whilst the wing logo features on the ankle collar in black. Underfoot, an OG Air Jordan 1 sole unit, featuring a white midsole and black outsole. This sole unit houses Nike Air technology that guarantees comfort whether you are wearing them on the court or the street. A must-have sneaker for any collector looking to turn heads this Summer, be sure to pick up a pair before its too late.

fields.name: Air Jordan 1 Mid
fields.description: Add a splash of bright and warm citrus to your next pair of sneakers with this fun and summer-themed pair of Air Jordan 1 Mid SE Bright Citrus Womens. If you’re a fan of dependable white sneakers, then add a touch of bright colour with this rich citrus shade showcased on the side leather panels and the front toe box — complete with air holes for full breathability, too. Your Nike swoosh is printed in clean white against a backdrop of lively citrus, and to contrast, the Air Jordan wings logo is stamped in orange against white. White laces with a subtle stitching effect complete the fresh and clean look, with cushioned comfort and support at all times with the Nike Air sole. Clean white panelling and midsole around the bottom of the sneaker break up the bright citrus shade of the Womens Air Jordan 1 Mid SE Bright Citrus

fields.name: Air Jordan 1 Mid
fields.description: The Air Jordan 1 Mid Chicago Toe is one of the most classic colourways in the collection. Featuring the iconic swoosh and wings logo on the side panels of the shoe. The premium feel of the black, red and white leather combination on the Jordan 1 Mid Chicago Toe makes it a perfect addition to any sneakerhead's collection

fields.description: A sweet spin on a passionate colorway, the Candy Red line sets the tone by uniting scarlet Visetos and nappa leather. An uncompromising merger of form and function, the Stark backpack features multiple exterior pockets as well as polished side stud embellishments. Made for the modern global nomad, the soft cotton twill interior features spacious compartments for your laptop and tablet.
